  <!-- ============= Introduction ============================== -->
  <chapter id="introduction">
    <title>What is the Ubuntu Software Store?</title>
    <para>
    The Ubuntu Software Store is a virtual catalog of thousands of free
    applications available for Ubuntu.
    You can find applications by category or by searching,
    and you can install an application with the click of a button.
    </para>
    <para>
      The Store also lets you examine the applications that are installed
      already,
      and remove those you no longer need.
    </para>
